                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13008912" author="brian.stansberry" created="Mon, 6 Oct 2014 11:12:53 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;My theory about the logging happening because a cause was attached is incorrect. It&apos;s logged because it happens at Stage.RUNTIME. RUNTIME OFEs are logged as there is the potential they have disrupted the server.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Solution is to not throw the OFE but rather to use context.getFailureDescription() to report the failure to the client.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
